headlines.description: — Ben Simmons, Joel Embiid and Tobias Harris each scored 18 points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 126-104 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers use balanced scoring, rout Hawks for 2nd straight game

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown hit a 3-pointer with 16.7 seconds remaining in overtime, Jayson Tatum scored a career-high 60 points and the Boston Celtics rallied from a 32-point deficit to beat the San Antonio Spurs 143-140 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics rally from 32-point deficit, top Spurs 143-140 in OT

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook posted his 31st triple-double of the season with 15 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists, and the Washington Wizards continued their postseason push with a 122-93 rout of the Cleveland Cavaliers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook posts 31st triple-double, Wizards rout Cavs 122-93

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 32 points, nine assists and seven rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Brooklyn Nets 128-109 on Friday night to remain unbeaten halfway through an important road trip.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Blazers pull away from Nets, stay unbeaten on trip

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 20 points, Jonas Valanciunas added 14 points and 15 rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Orlando Magic 92-75 on Friday as both teams shot poorly.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks has 20 as poor-shooting Grizzlies defeat Magic 92-75

headlines.description: — Brook Lopez and Khris Middleton each scored 22 points, and the Milwaukee Bucks were good enough without Giannis Antetokounmpo to beat the Chicago Bulls 108-98 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks roll past Bulls 108-98 without injured Antetokounmpo

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 31 points, Mikal Bridges added 18 and the Phoenix Suns pulled into a tie for the top spot in the Western Conference by beating the Utah Jazz 121-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns beat Jazz 121-100, pull into tie at top of West

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers
